


       
      It's funny, how the most sane, stable person can snap just so easily. And the ones that seem the craziest are the ones who show the least emotion.  My lip gives an involuntary quiver. A pain flashes in my chest. A chill races through my body. I know I'm losing it, but I don't know why.  My eyes half close. My body stiffens. My muscles tensen. What are you trying to do to me...  ...friend...
     

    
